Internet Printing Protocol (IPP) Registrations

Created
2002-07-15
Last Updated
2017-02-15
Available Formats

XML
HTML
Plain text

Registries included below

  • Objects
  • Attributes
  • Keyword Attribute Values
  • Enum Attribute Values
  • Attribute Group Tags
  • Out-of-Band Attribute Value Tags
  • Attribute Syntaxes
  • Operations
  • Status Codes

Objects

Registration Procedure(s)
Specification Required
Expert(s)

      

      
Reference

      
[RFC8011]

      
Note

      

        
In accordance with Sections 7 and 7.1 of [RFC8011],
proposed registrations must be submitted to a mailing list for review
by IESG-designated experts.

Objects are listed in alphabetic order. The specifications that define
objects also define operations and attributes for the objects.
    

      

      
Available Formats

      

        
CSV

          Reference

Attributes

    

      
Registration Procedure(s)

      

        
Expert Review

      

      
Expert(s)

      

        

      

      
Reference

      
[RFC8011]

      
Note

      

        
In accordance with Sections 7 and 7.2 of [RFC8011],
proposed registrations must be submitted to a mailing list for review
by IESG-designated experts.

Attributes are listed in alphabetic order. The member attributes of
collection attributes [RFC3382] are indented two spaces immediately
after the collection attribute to which they belong.

The "xxx" Job Template attributes are Job object attributes, while
the "xxx-default" and "xxx-supported" Job Template attributes are
Printer object attributes.  See [RFC8011] Section 5.2
Job Template Attributes.

The "xxx" Subscription Template attributes are Subscription object
attributes, while the "xxx-default" and "xxx-supported" Subscription
Template attributes are Printer object attributes.† See [RFC3995]
Section 5.2 Subscription Template Attributes.

Attribute Group Tags

    

      
Registration Procedure(s)

      

        
Specification Required

      

      
Expert(s)

      

        

      

      
Reference

      
[RFC8011]

      
Note

      

        
Attribute Group Tags, Out-of-Band Attribute Value Tags, and Attribute
Syntaxes share the same number space.

In accordance with Sections 7 and 7.5 of [RFC8011],
proposed registrations must be submitted to a mailing list for review
by IESG-designated experts.

The range of Attribute Group Tags is 0x00 to 0x0F. See [RFC8010]
Section 3.5.1.  The tag values are listed in numeric order.
    

      

      
Available Formats

      

        
CSV
      

    

    

      
        

          Value
          Name
          Reference
        

      
      
        

          0x00
          Reserved
          [RFC8010]
        

        

          0x01
          "operation-attributes-tag"
          [RFC8010]
        

        

          0x02
          "job-attributes-tag"
          [RFC8010]
        

        

          0x03
          "end-of-attributes-tag"
          [RFC8010]
        

        

          0x04
          "printer-attributes-tag"
          [RFC8010]
        

        

          0x05
          "unsupported-attributes-tag"
          [RFC8010]
        

        

          0x06
          "subscription-attributes-tag"
          [RFC3995]
        

        

          0x07
          "event-notification-attributes-tag"
          [RFC3995]
        

        

          0x08
          Reserved (ipp-get-resources)
          
        

        

          0x09
          document-attributes-tag
          [PWG5100.5]
        

        

          0x0A-0x0F
          Unassigned

Registration Procedure(s)

      

        
Specification Required

      

      
Expert(s)

[RFC8011]

      
Note

      

        
Attribute Group Tags, Out-of-Band Attribute Value Tags, and Attribute
Syntaxes share the same number space.

In accordance with Sections 7 and 7.6 of [RFC8011],
proposed registrations must be submitted to a mailing list for review
by IESG-designated experts.

The range of out-of-band tags is 0x10 to 0x1F. See [RFC8010]
Section 3.5.2.  The tag values are listed in numeric order.

Attribute Syntaxes

    

      
Registration Procedure(s)

      

        
Specification Required

      

      
Expert(s)

      

        

      

      
Reference

      
[RFC8011]

      
Note

      

        
Attribute Group Tags, Out-of-Band Attribute Value Tags, and Attribute
Syntaxes share the same number space.

In accordance with Sections 7 and 7.7 of [RFC8011],
proposed registrations must be submitted to a mailing list for review
by IESG-designated experts.

The range of attribute syntaxes is 0x20 to 0xFF. Use of the 0x7F value
permits additional values up to 0x3FFFFFFF for Specification Required
action and 0x40000000 to 0x7FFFFFFF for vendor extensions.  See
[RFC8010] Section 3.5.2.  The tag values are listed in
numeric order.
    

      

      
Available Formats

      

        
CSV
      

    

    

      
        

          Value
          Name
          Reference
        

      
      
        

          0x20
          Unassigned; can be assigned to 'generic integer' if it should ever be needed
          [RFC8010]
        

        

          0x21
          integer
          [RFC8010]
        

        

          0x22
          boolean
          [RFC8010]
        

        

          0x23
          enum
          [RFC8010]
        

        

          0x24-0x2F
          Unassigned integer data types

Expert Review

      

      
Expert(s)

      

        

      

      
Reference

      
[RFC8011]

      
Note

      

        
In accordance with Sections 7 and 7.8 of [RFC8011],
proposed registrations must be submitted to a mailing list for review
by IESG-designated experts.

See the hex values assigned to each operation under the
"operations-supported" attribute in Section 4 above.  In addition,
vendors may define their own private operations. See the explanation
at the beginning of Section 4 above on the enum allocation for such
vendor-defined private operations.

Operations are listed in alphabetic order. Specifications that extend
the semantics of operations defined in other specifications will be
listed here as well on separate lines with the notation "(extension)"
after the name.

Status Codes

    

      
Registration Procedure(s)

      

        
Expert Review

      

      
Expert(s)

      

        

      

      
Reference

      
[RFC8011]

      
Note

      

        
In accordance with Sections 7 and 7.9 of [RFC8011],
proposed registrations must be submitted to a mailing list for review
by IESG-designated experts.

The range of status code values is 0x0000 to 0x7FFF. Appendix B of
[RFC8011] allocates the value ranges for each status
code class as follows:

  "successful"     - 0x0000 to 0x00FF
  "informational"  - 0x0100 to 0x01FF
  Unassigned       - 0x0200 to 0x02FF
  "redirection"    - 0x0300 to 0x03FF
  "client-error"   - 0x0400 to 0x04FF
  "server-error"   - 0x0500 to 0x05FF
  Unassigned       - 0x0600 to 0x7FFF

The top half (128 values) of each range (0x0n80 to 0x0nFF,
for n = 0 to 5) is reserved for vendor use within each status code
class. Status codes are listed in numeric order.
